  "body": "`forge verify-contract` expects `./out/dapp.sol.json` file, but `forge build` output another format `./out/ContractName.sol/ContractName.json`.\r\n\r\nSo when trying to verify the contract, it will always error like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfoundry-optimism on üå± master [‚úò?]\r\n‚ùØ forge verify-contract src/Foundry.sol:Foundry 0x51421A04483F4006cEeb66cb2c917F9699ef7419\r\nDec 26 22:22:32.144 ERROR forge: error=No such file or directory (os error 2)\r\nError:\r\n   0: No such file or directory (os error 2)\r\n\r\nLocation:\r\n   /rustc/f1edd0429582dd29cccacaf50fd134b05593bd9c/library/core/src/result.rs:1914\r\n\r\nBacktrace omitted.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/gakonst/foundry/blob/master/cli/src/utils.rs#L62-L66\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/gakonst/foundry/blob/master/cli/src/cmd/verify.rs#L43",
